{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 1005 (PR #3422) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/3422.","id":"vf_723d61e0c8152764","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1005: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $\\frac{a_1}{b_1},\\frac{a_2}{b_2},\\ldots$ be the Farey fractions of order $n\\geq 4$. Let $f(n)$ be the largest integer such that if $1\\leq k<l\\leq k+f(n)$ then $\\frac{a_k}{b_k}$ and $\\frac{a_l}{b_l}$ are similarly ordered - in other words,\\[(a_k-a_l)(b_k-b_l)\\geq 0.\\]Estimate $f(n)$ - in particular, is there a constant $c>0$ such that $f(n)=(c+o(1))n$ for all large $n$? Current best: van Doorn \\cite{vD25b} has proved that\\[\\left(\\frac{1}{12}-o(1)\\right)n\\leq f(n) \\leq \\frac{1}{4}n+O(1),\\]and conjectures that the upper bound is optimal. Prize: no. OEIS: A386893. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_cc9994e4469679a7","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/1005.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_723d61e0c8152764","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:1005","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_723d61e0c8152764","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"vf_cc9994e4469679a7","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_cc9994e4469679a7","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":